Durban-  Ayanda Shezi, one of the accused in the murder of Glazer Motors petrol station owner Kidesh Ramjettan appeared in the Durban Regional Court on Monday. Wearing a black pants, T-Shirt and holding a black woollen hat In his hand Shezi heard in court that two additional charges were added to his murder charge. Prosecutor Surekha Marimuthu said he will also be charged with the possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition. He was remanded back into police custody until November 1. His co-accused Menziwa Mdakana and Zakhele Dubazane, who are in  Westville Correctional Services, will appear in the Durban Magistrates Court on November 22. Ramjettan was shot dead outside his Rossburgh business in August.  Ramjettan was standing in the parking lot of his Glazer Motors petrol station in Clairwood when a gunman walked up to him and shot him in the head. He died at the scene. Daily News